 JCL is the script language used to control the execution of programs in
IBM's batch systems. JCL has a very {fascist} syntax, and some versions will,
for example, {barf} if two spaces appear where it expects one. Most
programmers confronted with JCL simply copy a working file (or card deck),
changing the file names. Someone who actually understands and generates
unique JCL is regarded with the mixed respect one gives to someone who
memorizes the phone book. It is reported that hackers at IBM itself sometimes
sing "Who's the breeder of the crud that mangles you and me? I-B-M,